"adj. 好说教的；简要的 【英】 adj. 好说教的(abounding in excessive moralizing)；简要的(terse; pithy) 【记】 sentence(句子)+ious →一个句子说完→简 要的 adj. 好说教的; 简要的; 警句的 【记】源于: sentence(n 句子) 【记】源自sentence 句子，说话好用格言警句的，这样好说教，也简洁 sententious (adj.)  mid-15c., ""full of meaning,"" from Middle French sententieux, from Latin sententiosus ""full of meaning, pithy,"" from sententia ""thought; expression of a thought"" (see sentence (n.)). Meaning ""addicted to pompous moralizing"" first recorded 1590s. Related: Sententiously; sententiousness."
